# Docs stay in sync with the site

When you **create, update, or delete** anything on the website, check whether docs need the same change. Do not leave docs describing old behaviour.

## Source of truth

| What changed | Update in code first | Then update docs |
|--------------|---------------------|------------------|
| Brand colours, fonts, tokens | `src/app/globals.css` | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md` §6, `.cursor/rules/open-decisions.mdc`, `.cursor/skills/project-brief/SKILL.md`, `README.md` if stack/colours listed |
| Contact, hours, service area | `src/lib/site.ts`, `src/lib/contact.ts` | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md` §1–2, `docs/CLIENT_QUESTIONNAIRE.md`, `.cursor/rules/open-decisions.mdc` |
| Services (add/remove/rename) | `src/lib/content/services.ts`, `public/images/services/` | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md` §1 services list, `.cursor/skills/project-brief/SKILL.md` |
| Copy, CTAs, section structure | `src/lib/content/*`, components | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md` if it documents that section; skills if they summarise structure |
| Images / assets | `public/images/**` | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md` §6 imagery or checklist if asset inventory is tracked |
| Confirmed client decisions (D1–D10) | relevant `src/` files | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md` §2, `docs/CLIENT_QUESTIONNAIRE.md`, `.cursor/rules/open-decisions.mdc` |
| Scope (new pages, features) | app routes, components | `docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md`, `.cursor/rules/project-scope.mdc` if in/out of scope shifts |

## Workflow

1. Make the site change.
2. Scan the table above for affected doc files.
3. Update docs in the **same task** — do not defer unless the user explicitly asked for code-only.
4. If a doc value is duplicated in multiple places, update **all** of them (especially `open-decisions.mdc` and `PROJECT_BRIEF.md`).

## Rules

- **Code wins** — if docs and `src/` disagree, fix the docs to match the live site.
- **Do not invent** client facts in docs; only record confirmed values (see `open-decisions.mdc`).
- **Skip trivial UI tweaks** (spacing, hover states) unless the brief explicitly documents that detail.
- **Mention doc updates** in your summary when you changed both code and docs.

## Image convention

Service images live at `public/images/services/{service-id}.png` where `{service-id}` matches `ServiceId` in `src/lib/content/services.ts`.
